#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:245
msgid ""
"Using the shell, you can try selecting elements using `CSS`_ with the "
"response object:"
msgstr "使用 shell，您可以尝试使用 `CSS`_ 来选择响应对象："

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:252
msgid ""
">>> response.css(\"title\")\n"
"[<Selector query='descendant-or-self::title' data='<title>Quotes to Scrape</"
"title>'>]"
msgstr ""
">>>> response.css(\"title\")\n"
"[<Selector query='descendant-or-self::title' data='<title>Quotes to scrak</"
"title>'>]"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:257
msgid ""
"The result of running ``response.css('title')`` is a list-like object "
"called :class:`~scrapy.selector.SelectorList`, which represents a list of :"
"class:`~scrapy.Selector` objects that wrap around XML/HTML elements and "
"allow you to run further queries to refine the selection or extract the data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:263
msgid "To extract the text from the title above, you can do:"
msgstr "要从上面的标题中提取文本，您可以做："

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:265
msgid ""
">>> response.css(\"title::text\").getall()\n"
"['Quotes to Scrape']"
msgstr ""
">>> response.css(\"title::text\").getall()\n"
"['引用到Scrape']"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:270
msgid ""
"There are two things to note here: one is that we've added ``::text`` to the "
"CSS query, to mean we want to select only the text elements directly inside "
"``<title>`` element.  If we don't specify ``::text``, we'd get the full "
"title element, including its tags:"
msgstr ""
"这里有两件事需要注意：一个是我们已经将 ``:text`` 添加到CSS 查询中。 表示我们"
"只想在``<title>`` 元素中选择文本元素。 如果我们没有指定 ``::text`` ，我们将得"
"到完整的标题元素，包括其标签："

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:275
msgid ""
">>> response.css(\"title\").getall()\n"
"['<title>Quotes to Scrape</title>']"
msgstr ""
">>> response.css(\"title\").getall()\n"
"['<title>Quotes to Scrak</title>']"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:280
msgid ""
"The other thing is that the result of calling ``.getall()`` is a list: it is "
"possible that a selector returns more than one result, so we extract them "
"all. When you know you just want the first result, as in this case, you can "
"do:"
msgstr ""
"另一件事是调用 ``的结果。 etall()`` 是一个列表：一个选择器可能返回多个结果，"
"所以我们可以提取所有的结果。 当你知道你只是想要第一个结果，就像在这种情况下那"
"样, 你可以做："

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:284
msgid ""
">>> response.css(\"title::text\").get()\n"
"'Quotes to Scrape'"
msgstr ""
">>> response.css(\"title::text\").get()\n"
"'引用到 Scrape'"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:289
msgid "As an alternative, you could've written:"
msgstr "作为替代，您可以写入："

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:291
msgid ""
">>> response.css(\"title::text\")[0].get()\n"
"'Quotes to Scrape'"
msgstr ""
">>> response.css(\"title::text\")[0].get()\n"
"'Quotes to Scrape'"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:296
msgid ""
"Accessing an index on a :class:`~scrapy.selector.SelectorList` instance will "
"raise an :exc:`IndexError` exception if there are no results:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:299
msgid ""
">>> response.css(\"noelement\")[0].get()\n"
"Traceback (most recent call last):\n"
"...\n"
"IndexError: list index out of range"
msgstr ""
">>>>> response.css(\"noelement\")[0].get()\n"
"Tracetback(最近一次通话):\n"
"...\n"
"Index错误：列表索引超出范围"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:306
msgid ""
"You might want to use ``.get()`` directly on the :class:`~scrapy.selector."
"SelectorList` instance instead, which returns ``None`` if there are no "
"results:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:310
msgid ">>> response.css(\"noelement\").get()"
msgstr ">>> response.css(\"noelement\").get()"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:314
msgid ""
"There's a lesson here: for most scraping code, you want it to be resilient "
"to errors due to things not being found on a page, so that even if some "
"parts fail to be scraped, you can at least get **some** data."
msgstr ""
"这里有一个课程：对于大多数拆解代码，你希望它能够对因为在页面上找不到的事情而"
"产生的错误做出弹性反应， 这样即使有些部件未被拆除，您至少可以获得**一些** 数"
"据。"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:318
msgid ""
"Besides the :meth:`~scrapy.selector.SelectorList.getall` and :meth:`~scrapy."
"selector.SelectorList.get` methods, you can also use the :meth:`~scrapy."
"selector.SelectorList.re` method to extract using :doc:`regular expressions "
"<library/re>`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:323
msgid ""
">>> response.css(\"title::text\").re(r\"Quotes.*\")\n"
"['Quotes to Scrape']\n"
">>> response.css(\"title::text\").re(r\"Q\\w+\")\n"
"['Quotes']\n"
">>> response.css(\"title::text\").re(r\"(\\w+) to (\\w+)\")\n"
"['Quotes', 'Scrape']"
msgstr ""
">>>> response.css(\"title::text\").re(r\"Quotes.*\")\n"
"['quotes to scrape']\n"
">>> > response.css(\"title::text\").re(r\"Q\\w+\")\n"
"[''Quotes']\n"
">>> > response.css(\"title::text\").re(r\"(\\w+) to (\\w+)\")\n"
"['quotes', 'Scrape']"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:332
msgid ""
"In order to find the proper CSS selectors to use, you might find it useful "
"to open the response page from the shell in your web browser using "
"``view(response)``. You can use your browser's developer tools to inspect "
"the HTML and come up with a selector (see :ref:`topics-developer-tools`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:337
msgid ""
"`Selector Gadget`_ is also a nice tool to quickly find CSS selector for "
"visually selected elements, which works in many browsers."
msgstr ""
"`Selector Gadget`_ 也是一个很好的工具，可以快速找到用于视觉选择的元素的 CSS "
"选择器，这些元素在许多浏览器中起作用。"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:344
msgid "XPath: a brief intro"
msgstr "XPath：简短介绍"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:346
msgid ""
"Besides `CSS`_, Scrapy selectors also support using `XPath`_ expressions:"
msgstr "除了`CSS`_之外，Scrapy 选择器也支持使用 `XPath`_ 表达式："

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:348
msgid ""
">>> response.xpath(\"//title\")\n"
"[<Selector query='//title' data='<title>Quotes to Scrape</title>'>]\n"
">>> response.xpath(\"//title/text()\").get()\n"
"'Quotes to Scrape'"
msgstr ""
">>>> response.xpath(\"//title\")\n"
"[<Selector query='//title' data='<title>Quotes to Scrak</title>'>]\n"
">> > response.xpath(\"//title/text()\").get()\n"
"'Quotes to Scrape'"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:355
msgid ""
"XPath expressions are very powerful, and are the foundation of Scrapy "
"Selectors. In fact, CSS selectors are converted to XPath under-the-hood. You "
"can see that if you read the text representation of the selector objects in "
"the shell closely."
msgstr ""
"XPath 表达式非常强大，是废料选择器的基础。事实上，CSS 选择器会转换为 XPath 底"
"层。 您可以看到如果您仔细阅读外壳中选择器对象的文本表达式。"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:360
msgid ""
"While perhaps not as popular as CSS selectors, XPath expressions offer more "
"power because besides navigating the structure, it can also look at the "
"content. Using XPath, you're able to select things like: *the link that "
"contains the text \"Next Page\"*. This makes XPath very fitting to the task "
"of scraping, and we encourage you to learn XPath even if you already know "
"how to construct CSS selectors, it will make scraping much easier."
msgstr ""
"虽然XPath 表达式可能不像CSS 选择器那么受欢迎，但它提供了更多的力量，因为除了"
"导航结构外，它还可以查看内容。 使用 XPath，您可以选择如下内容：*包含文本\"下"
"一页\"的链接。 这使XPath 非常适合拆解任务， 我们鼓励您学习XPath ，即使您已经"
"知道如何构建CSS 选择器，它也会使拆解变得更容易。"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:367
msgid ""
"We won't cover much of XPath here, but you can read more about :ref:`using "
"XPath with Scrapy Selectors here <topics-selectors>`. To learn more about "
"XPath, we recommend `this tutorial to learn XPath through examples <http://"
"zvon.org/comp/r/tut-XPath_1.html>`_, and `this tutorial to learn \"how to "
"think in XPath\" <http://plasmasturm.org/log/xpath101/>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:377
msgid "Extracting quotes and authors"
msgstr "正在提取引用和作者"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:379
msgid ""
"Now that you know a bit about selection and extraction, let's complete our "
"spider by writing the code to extract the quotes from the web page."
msgstr ""
"现在你有点关于选择和提取， 让我们通过写代码从网页提取引文来完成我们的蜘蛛。"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:382
