#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:515
msgid "Storing the scraped data"
msgstr "存储废料数据"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:517
msgid ""
"The simplest way to store the scraped data is by using :ref:`Feed exports "
"<topics-feed-exports>`, with the following command::"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:520
msgid "scrapy crawl quotes -O quotes.json"
msgstr "scray crawl quotes -O quotes.json"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:522
msgid ""
"That will generate a ``quotes.json`` file containing all scraped items, "
"serialized in `JSON`_."
msgstr ""
"这将生成一个 ``quotes.json`` 文件，其中包含所有被卷轴的物品，并在 `JSON` 中序"
"列化。"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:525
msgid ""
"The ``-O`` command-line switch overwrites any existing file; use ``-o`` "
"instead to append new content to any existing file. However, appending to a "
"JSON file makes the file contents invalid JSON. When appending to a file, "
"consider using a different serialization format, such as `JSON Lines`_::"
msgstr ""
"``-O`` 命令行切换覆盖任何现有的文件。使用 ``-o`` 代替将新内容添加到任何现有文"
"件中。 但是，附加到 JSON 文件使文件内容无效 JSON 。 当附加到一个文件时，考虑"
"使用不同的序列化格式，例如`JSON Lines`_:"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:530
msgid "scrapy crawl quotes -o quotes.jsonl"
msgstr "scrapy crawl quotes -o quotes.jsonl"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:532
msgid ""
"The `JSON Lines`_ format is useful because it's stream-like, so you can "
"easily append new records to it. It doesn't have the same problem as JSON "
"when you run twice. Also, as each record is a separate line, you can process "
"big files without having to fit everything in memory, there are tools like "
"`JQ`_ to help do that at the command-line."
msgstr ""
"`JSON Lines`_ 格式是有用的，因为它与流相似，所以你可以轻松地将新记录附加到"
"它。 当你运行两次时，它与JSON不存在相同的问题。 此外，由于每条记录都是单独的"
"一行，您可以处理大文件，而不必将所有文件都放在内存中。 有一些工具，例如`JQ`_ "
"来帮助在命令行进行这种操作。"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:538
msgid ""
"In small projects (like the one in this tutorial), that should be enough. "
"However, if you want to perform more complex things with the scraped items, "
"you can write an :ref:`Item Pipeline <topics-item-pipeline>`. A placeholder "
"file for Item Pipelines has been set up for you when the project is created, "
"in ``tutorial/pipelines.py``. Though you don't need to implement any item "
"pipelines if you just want to store the scraped items."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:550
msgid "Following links"
msgstr "关注链接"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:552
msgid ""
"Let's say, instead of just scraping the stuff from the first two pages from "
"https://quotes.toscrape.com, you want quotes from all the pages in the "
"website."
msgstr ""
"让我们说，不要只是从https://quotes.toscrape.com的头两个页面中拆除物品，你想要"
"从网站中的所有页面中引用。"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:555
msgid ""
"Now that you know how to extract data from pages, let's see how to follow "
"links from them."
msgstr "现在你知道如何从页面提取数据，让我们看看如何从它们中跟进链接。"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:558
msgid ""
"The first thing to do is extract the link to the page we want to follow.  "
"Examining our page, we can see there is a link to the next page with the "
"following markup:"
msgstr ""
"第一件事是提取链接到我们想要遵循的页面。 查看我们的页面，我们可以看到一个链接"
"到下一个页面的标记："

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:562
msgid ""
"<ul class=\"pager\">\n"
"    <li class=\"next\">\n"
"        <a href=\"/page/2/\">Next <span aria-hidden=\"true\">&rarr;</span></"
"a>\n"
"    </li>\n"
"</ul>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:570
msgid "We can try extracting it in the shell:"
msgstr "我们可以尝试在炮弹中提取它："

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:575
msgid ""
"This gets the anchor element, but we want the attribute ``href``. For that, "
"Scrapy supports a CSS extension that lets you select the attribute contents, "
"like this:"
msgstr ""
"这就得到了锚点元素，但我们想要属性 'href`` 。 为此，Scrapy 支持 CSS 扩展，使"
"您可以选择属性内容，例如："

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:579
msgid ""
">>> response.css(\"li.next a::attr(href)\").get()\n"
"'/page/2/'"
msgstr ""
">>> response.css(\"li.next a::attr(href)\").get()\n"
"'/page/2/'"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:584
msgid ""
"There is also an ``attrib`` property available (see :ref:`selecting-"
"attributes` for more):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:587
msgid ""
">>> response.css(\"li.next a\").attrib[\"href\"]\n"
"'/page/2/'"
msgstr ""
">>> response.css(\"li.next a\").attrib[\"href\"]\n"
"'/page/2/'"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:592
msgid ""
"Now let's see our spider, modified to recursively follow the link to the "
"next page, extracting data from it:"
msgstr "现在让我们看到我们的蜘蛛，修改后递归跟着链接到下一页，从它中提取数据："

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:595
msgid ""
"import scrapy\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"class QuotesSpider(scrapy.Spider):\n"
"    name = \"quotes\"\n"
"    start_urls = [\n"
"        \"https://quotes.toscrape.com/page/1/\",\n"
"    ]\n"
"\n"
"    def parse(self, response):\n"
"        for quote in response.css(\"div.quote\"):\n"
"            yield {\n"
"                \"text\": quote.css(\"span.text::text\").get(),\n"
"                \"author\": quote.css(\"small.author::text\").get(),\n"
"                \"tags\": quote.css(\"div.tags a.tag::text\").getall(),\n"
"            }\n"
"\n"
"        next_page = response.css(\"li.next a::attr(href)\").get()\n"
"        if next_page is not None:\n"
"            next_page = response.urljoin(next_page)\n"
"            yield scrapy.Request(next_page, callback=self.parse)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:620
msgid ""
"Now, after extracting the data, the ``parse()`` method looks for the link to "
"the next page, builds a full absolute URL using the :meth:`~scrapy.http."
"Response.urljoin` method (since the links can be relative) and yields a new "
"request to the next page, registering itself as callback to handle the data "
"extraction for the next page and to keep the crawling going through all the "
"pages."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:627
msgid ""
"What you see here is Scrapy's mechanism of following links: when you yield a "
"Request in a callback method, Scrapy will schedule that request to be sent "
"and register a callback method to be executed when that request finishes."
msgstr ""
"你在这里看到的是废料的以下链接机制：当你在回调方法中发出请求， Scrapy 将安排"
"发送请求的时间并注册一个回调方法在请求完成后执行。"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:631
msgid ""
"Using this, you can build complex crawlers that follow links according to "
"rules you define, and extract different kinds of data depending on the page "
"it's visiting."
msgstr ""
"使用这个，您可以根据您定义的规则构建跟随链接的复杂的 crawler ， 并根据所访问"
"的页面提取不同类型的数据。"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:635
msgid ""
"In our example, it creates a sort of loop, following all the links to the "
"next page until it doesn't find one -- handy for crawling blogs, forums and "
"other sites with pagination."
msgstr ""
"在我们的例子中，它创造了一种循环， 关注所有链接到下一个页面直到找不到一个-便"
"捷地浏览博客、论坛和其他带分页的站点。"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:643
msgid "A shortcut for creating Requests"
msgstr "创建请求的快捷方式"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:645
msgid ""
"As a shortcut for creating Request objects you can use :meth:`response."
"follow <scrapy.http.TextResponse.follow>`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:648
msgid ""
"import scrapy\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"class QuotesSpider(scrapy.Spider):\n"
"    name = \"quotes\"\n"
"    start_urls = [\n"
"        \"https://quotes.toscrape.com/page/1/\",\n"
"    ]\n"
"\n"
"    def parse(self, response):\n"
"        for quote in response.css(\"div.quote\"):\n"
"            yield {\n"
"                \"text\": quote.css(\"span.text::text\").get(),\n"
"                \"author\": quote.css(\"span small::text\").get(),\n"
"                \"tags\": quote.css(\"div.tags a.tag::text\").getall(),\n"
"            }\n"
"\n"
"        next_page = response.css(\"li.next a::attr(href)\").get()\n"
"        if next_page is not None:\n"
"            yield response.follow(next_page, callback=self.parse)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:671
msgid ""
"Unlike scrapy.Request, ``response.follow`` supports relative URLs directly - "
"no need to call urljoin. Note that ``response.follow`` just returns a "
"Request instance; you still have to yield this Request."
msgstr ""
"不同于scrapy.Request, ``response.follow`` 直接支持相对的 URL - 无需调用 "
"urljoin。 请注意，``response.follow`` 只是返回了一个请求实例；您仍然必须提交"
"此请求。"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:677
msgid ""
"You can also pass a selector to ``response.follow`` instead of a string; "
"this selector should extract necessary attributes:"
msgstr ""
"你也可以传递一个选择器到 ``response.follow`` 而不是一个字符串；这个选择器应该"
"提取必要的属性："

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:680
msgid ""
"for href in response.css(\"ul.pager a::attr(href)\"):\n"
"    yield response.follow(href, callback=self.parse)"
msgstr ""
"用于响应.css(\"ul.pager a:ttran(href)\":\n"
"    yound response.follow(href, callback=self.parse)"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:685
msgid ""
"For ``<a>`` elements there is a shortcut: ``response.follow`` uses their "
"href attribute automatically. So the code can be shortened further:"
msgstr ""
"对于``<a>`` 元素，存在一个快捷方式： ``response.follow`` 自动使用它们的 href "
"属性。所以代码可以进一步缩短："

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:688
msgid ""
"for a in response.css(\"ul.pager a\"):\n"
"    yield response.follow(a, callback=self.parse)"
msgstr ""
"用于响应.css(\"ul.pager a\"):\n"
"    red response.follow(a, callback=self.parse)"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:693
msgid ""
"To create multiple requests from an iterable, you can use :meth:`response."
"follow_all <scrapy.http.TextResponse.follow_all>` instead:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:696
msgid ""
"anchors = response.css(\"ul.pager a\")\n"
"yield from response.follow_all(anchors, callback=self.parse)"
msgstr ""
"锚点 = response.css(\"ul.pager a\")\n"
"从响应, follow_all(锚, callback=self.parse)"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:701
msgid "or, shortening it further:"
msgstr "或进一步缩短："

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:703
msgid "yield from response.follow_all(css=\"ul.pager a\", callback=self.parse)"
msgstr "从 response.follow_all(css=\"ul.pager a\", callback=self.parse)"

