#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:743
msgid ""
"This spider will start from the main page, it will follow all the links to "
"the authors pages calling the ``parse_author`` callback for each of them, "
"and also the pagination links with the ``parse`` callback as we saw before."
msgstr ""
"这个旋转器将从主页开始， 它将跟随作者页面的所有链接，其中每个页面调用 "
"``parse_author`` 回调。 还有我们以前看到的 ``parse`` 回调的分页链接。"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:747
msgid ""
"Here we're passing callbacks to :meth:`response.follow_all <scrapy.http."
"TextResponse.follow_all>` as positional arguments to make the code shorter; "
"it also works for :class:`~scrapy.Request`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:752
msgid ""
"The ``parse_author`` callback defines a helper function to extract and "
"cleanup the data from a CSS query and yields the Python dict with the author "
"data."
msgstr ""
"``parse_author`` 回调定义了一个助手函数来提取和清理一个 CSS 查询的数据，并用"
"作者数据生成Python 词典。"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:755
msgid ""
"Another interesting thing this spider demonstrates is that, even if there "
"are many quotes from the same author, we don't need to worry about visiting "
"the same author page multiple times. By default, Scrapy filters out "
"duplicated requests to URLs already visited, avoiding the problem of hitting "
"servers too much because of a programming mistake. This can be configured in "
"the :setting:`DUPEFILTER_CLASS` setting."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:762
msgid ""
"Hopefully by now you have a good understanding of how to use the mechanism "
"of following links and callbacks with Scrapy."
msgstr "希望您现在能够很好地了解如何使用以下链接和回调的机制。"

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:765
msgid ""
"As yet another example spider that leverages the mechanism of following "
"links, check out the :class:`~scrapy.spiders.CrawlSpider` class for a "
"generic spider that implements a small rules engine that you can use to "
"write your crawlers on top of it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../intro/tutorial.rst:770
